All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CustomerAddress
    CustomerAddress contains all the necessary details to fully describe a customer's business address.
    DBConnection
    DBConnection encapsulates the underlying connectivity and query properties that make up the application's connection to the SQL Server database.
    DBService
    DBService extends the initial core DBConnection class and implements all logic and functionality for accessing the SQL Server back-end database.
    LoginController
    LoginController contains the logic and field references to the GUI controls on the Login form.
    LoginModel
    LoginModel contains the fields necessary to represent the model for the Login form.
    Main
    Main is used to launch the Java VM and then load the JavaFX runtime (for some reason, a class that extends Application is unable to load).
    PurchaseOrderProduct
    PurchaseOrderProduct contains the specific information about a product coming from a purchase order in the RMA database.
    RMA
    The RMA class starts the JavaFX runtime and launches the Login screen.
    RMADetailsFormController
    RMADetailsFormController contains the logic and field references to the GUI controls on the RMADetailScreen.
    RMADetailsFormModel
    RMADetailsFormModel contains extended fields from RMAFormModel that display in RMADetailScreen.
    RMAFormController
    RMAFormController contains the logic and field references to the GUI controls on the RMAForm.
    RMAFormModel
    RMAFormModel contains the fields and methods that make up the RMAForm model.
    RMAListViewController
    RMAListViewController contains the logic and field references to the GUI controls on the RMAListView form.
    RMAListViewModel
    RMAListViewModel contains the fields that make up the model for the RMAListView form.
